originalText.text: Please do not utilize this location if you value prompt contact and/or exceptional support. I'm sure the staff is overworked and needing assistance; However, they have not yet provided fair and just reason as to why they won't release my daughters funds (from her and her decedent father's account) after being provided all demanded documents. I have been in touch with CHASE complaints team, legal team, and decedent team- last I was told I need only go to the branch and have my daughter retrieve her money. The branch staff is a) saying I am lying and that no one has approved my minor grieving child to get her money and b) that they will "reach out" when they can. They only reach out when I blast them on social media. Someone please provide lawyer information so I can force them to give my daughter her money.

originalText.text: I have mixed feelings about this branch due to a wire incident a few months ago. Today I met with Mr. Sanchez. He was very attentive, I was just looking for CD, and information on opening my LLC. He was able to not only help me with what I needed but also, provided a-lot of helpful advice.

originalText.text: An absolute dump.  Smells like an ashtray.  We had an appointment with a private chase banker who was rude and rushed us through.  Completely not the Chase experience we were expecting after being to the CHASE private bank on 72nd.  Would not go again.

originalText.text:
My wife and I, who have longstanding accounts with Chase bank, wanted to open a joint account. We were asked unusual personal information and we were told that it is mandatory due to banking regulations.

When we asked to be shown supporting evidence that we need to provide this information, they said they were not able to.

Therefore we are moving our business to a more customer friendly bank.
